  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed development, by virtue of the inappropriate design and prominent location of the roof terrace, associated dormer and balustrade and roof lights would be a visually discordant feature failing to be sympathetic to the listed building and surroundings and would be harmful to the character and appearance of the Clerkenwell Green Conservation Area. This is contrary to policies D1 (Overall design), D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), and D22 (New development), D25 (Roof Extensions) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, Section 2.4 of the Islington Urban Design Guide 2006, para 1.20 and 1.22 of the Clerkenwell Green Conservation Area Design Guidelines and HE9.2 of PPS5: Planning for the Historic Environment."
